Interface StrParameterHandler<T>

Type Parameters:
T - the type that this handler handles
All Known Implementing Classes:
BooleanHandler, ByteHandler, DiscordMemberHandler, DiscordTextChannelHandler, DiscordUserHandler, DoubleHandler, FloatHandler, IntegerHandler, LongHandler, ShortHandler, SpigotPlayerHandler, SpigotWorldHandler, StringHandler
public interface StrParameterHandler<T>
Parameter handler for a certain type.

    • parse

      @NotNull T parse​(@NotNull @NotNull String text) throws Throwable
      Parse a string to this type.
      You can throw:
      • StrParameterHandler.StrWhichException to indicate multiple options (ambiguity)
      • StrParameterHandler.StrParseException to indicate parsing problems
      Parameters:
      text - the string to parse
      Returns:
      an instance of this type parsed from the string
      Throws:
      Throwable - when something else fails. (Exceptions don't have to be caught in the parser)

    • parseSafe

      @NotNull default T parseSafe​(@NotNull @NotNull String text) throws StrParameterHandler.StrWhichException, StrParameterHandler.StrParseException
      Safely parse.
      Converts all exceptions other than StrParameterHandler.StrWhichException or StrParameterHandler.StrParseException to StrParameterHandler.StrParseExceptions.
      Parameters:
      text - the string to parse
      Returns:
      an instance of this type parsed from the string
      Throws:
      StrParameterHandler.StrWhichException - when there are multiple options in a parser, based on the string
      StrParameterHandler.StrParseException - when a parser fails

    • getMultiplier

      default int getMultiplier​(@NotNull @NotNull AtomicReference<String> value)

      Parameters:

      Returns:
      the value, parsed.

    • multiplierFor

      default int multiplierFor​(char character) throws IllegalStateException
      Get the multiplier for some character (so that 10k can become 10000). Returns 1 for unlisted characters.
      1. c -> 16
      2. h -> 100
      3. r -> 512
      4. k -> 1000
      5. m -> 1000000
      6. default -> 1
      Parameters:
      character - the character to get the multiplier of
      Returns:
      the multiplier
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException
